nter edit summary should capture:\n- New bond formed: O:10–Si:20\n- Charge change: O:10 from -1 to 0; Si:20 from 0 to -1\n- Ring formation: 5-membered ring involving the carbon bearing O:10, two carbons, the carbonyl oxygen region, Si:20, and O:10\n\nLet me be more precise about the bond changes:\n\nIn reactant: O:10 is bonded to a carbon (the one bearing both branches), and Si:20 is bonded to the =O+ oxygen and three methyl groups.\n\nIn product: O:10 is bonded to Si:20 AND to the same carbon (ring closure C2...2), and Si:20 is bonded to =O+, O:10, and three methyl groups.\n\nSo the key bond change is:\n- Bond formed: O:10–Si:20\n\nAnd charge changes:\n- O:10: charge -1 → 0\n- Si:20: charge 0 → -1\n\nThe reaction center is the formation of the O:10–Si:20 bond with accompanying charge redistribution, creating a cyclic silyl enolate.\n\nFor the answer format \"reaction_edit_summary\", I should describe the bond edits and charge changes at the mapped atoms.\n\nReaction center: O:10–Si:20 bond formation; O:10 charge change (-1→0); Si:20 charge change (0→-1); ring closure forming 5-membered silyl enolate ring."
